      "*   **The Staff:** The staff is the foundation of written music. It consists of five horizontal lines and four spaces. Each line and space represents a specific musical pitch.\n",
      "\n",
      "*   **Clefs:** A clef assigns specific pitches to the lines and spaces of the staff. The two most common clefs are:\n",
      "    *   **Treble Clef (G Clef):** Usually used for higher-pitched instruments and voices. The curl of the clef circles the line representing the note G above middle C.\n",
      "    *   **Bass Clef (F Clef):** Usually used for lower-pitched instruments and voices. The two dots of the clef surround the line representing the note F below middle C.\n",
      "\n",
      "*   **Notes:** Notes represent musical pitches and their duration. The basic parts of a note are the notehead, stem, and flag (if applicable). Different types of notes represent different durations:\n",
